<bioghist altrender="biography" encodinganalog="545" id="a2">
	<head>Biography</head>
	<p>Author and illustrator of more than forty children's books. Owner of Chartier Gallery in <geogname>Brooklyn, CT</geogname>.</p>

<p></p>
</bioghist>
<scopecontent encodinganalog="520" id="a3">
<head>Scope and Content</head>
<p>The collection contains artwork, notes, correspondence, photographs and other materials pertaining to <persname> Normand Chartier</persname>'s illustrations of several children's books.</p>
</scopecontent>
<relatedmaterial encodinganalog="544 1" id="a6">
<head>Related Material</head>
<p>Archives &#x0026; Special Collections has a substantial collection of children's literature and associated artwork. For detailed information on these collections please contact the 
    <extref href="http://doddcenter.uconn.edu/asc/dodda2z/curatorinfo.cfm?curatorinfo=1">curator</extref> or ask at the reference desk. Illustrations of the work of <persname>Marjorie Sharmat</persname> can also be found in the <extref href="http://www.lib.uconn.edu/online/research/speclib/ASC/findaids/Simont/MSS19970002.html"><persname>Marc Simont</persname></extref> Papers.</p>
</relatedmaterial>
